Multithreadig:
---------------
in java we can instiate multiple thread to perform variuos tasks in the process simultaneously using multithreading.
In Java we can implement multithreading using 2 ways.
1. Exending Thread
    Steps: 
    1. make the class exends Thread class
    2. create object for the class 
    3. Invoke object.start() method. 
 
2. Implementing Runnable interface.
     1. Make the class Implement Runnable interface
     2. Create object for the class.
     3. Create Object for the Thread class and pass the object from step 2  to the thread class consructor. 
     4. invoke thread class Object start() method.


When to use what:
   When my class dont extend any other classes then we go for Approach 1.
   when my class extends any other class then we go for approach 2.